articles.content: Customs officers seized over 170 packets of cigarettes with duties unpaid. Following investigations, 12 people were issued compounded fines, with the amount ranging from $500 to $800. For every packet of duty-unpaid cigarettes, an offender can be fined $500. The public can report illegal activities to Singapore Customs online.
